Scritti Politti are a British band, originally formed 
in 1977 in Leeds, Yorkshire, England by Cardiff-born 
singer-songwriter Green Gartside. He is the only member 
of the band to have remained throughout the group's 
history.

Initially a left-wing-inspired post-punk British rock group, 
Scritti Politti developed into a more mainstream pop music 
project in the early to mid-1980s, enjoying significant 
success in the record charts in the UK and the US. The 
group's most successful album, 1985's Cupid & Psyche 85, 
spawned three UK Top 20 hits with "Wood Beez 
[Pray Like Aretha Franklin]", "Absolute", and "The Word Girl"
as well as a US Top 20 hit with "Perfect Way".
